    ('11df5329-1246-56ae-b034-b7bf165c9512', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'What is the primary purpose of the Emergency Medical Services (EMS) system''', 'To provide transportation to hospitals', 'To deliver emergency medical care to the critically ill and injured', 'To respond to all 911 calls', 'To replace hospital emergency departments', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. To deliver emergency medical care to the critically ill and injured', 'intermediate'),
    ('70dfd0e8-87fa-52a8-a4b9-0eccf27cf05b', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'Which of the following is a component of the NHTSA Technical Assistance Program Assessment Standards''', 'Equipment manufacturing standards', 'Pharmaceutical regulations', 'Public information and education', 'Hospital accreditation', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. Public information and education', 'intermediate'),
    ('3edce3ab-c95a-5050-b9e0-b344e4273a29', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'What is the minimum level of training identified in the EMS system hierarchy''', 'First Responder', 'EMT-Basic', 'EMT-Intermediate', 'EMT-Paramedic', 'option_a', 'Correct answer: A. First Responder', 'intermediate'),
    ('ddbbb5b2-b2e8-576b-920f-c10ea94c20c4', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'The EMT-Basic serves as which type of agent to the physician''', 'Independent agent', 'Designated agent', 'Primary agent', 'Supervising agent', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Designated agent', 'intermediate'),
    ('271ff146-281e-59c9-876f-4e67ed9d49f5', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'Quality improvement in EMS is defined as:', 'A system of punishment for errors', 'A system of internal/external reviews and audits to identify aspects needing improvement', 'A method of increasing ambulance response times', 'A system for reducing patient complaints', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. A system of internal/external reviews and audits to identify aspects needing improvement', 'intermediate'),
    ('1327b7a4-91dd-5f51-a328-82f996f63aa7', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'Medical direction can be classified as:', 'Primary and secondary', 'On-line and off-line', 'Direct and indirect', 'Active and passive', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. On-line and off-line', 'intermediate'),
    ('b623634f-ed5b-5c76-a3a2-a96a1153af2f', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'Which is an example of off-line medical direction''', 'Telephone consultation with a physician', 'Radio communication with medical control', 'Protocols and standing orders', 'Direct physician presence on scene', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. Protocols and standing orders', 'intermediate'),
    ('bae7b94b-960c-5179-8210-ebb0fa3b7508', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'The care rendered by an EMT-Basic is considered:', 'Independent medical practice', 'An extension of the medical director''s authority', 'Nursing care', 'First aid only', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. An extension of the medical director''s authority', 'intermediate'),
    ('3d08df76-1a0b-59b5-9812-fb62c5477b6d', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'Which of the following is a professional attribute expected of an EMT-Basic''', 'Maintaining up-to-date knowledge and skills', 'Wearing casual clothing to calls', 'Working independently without consultation', 'Avoiding continuing education', 'option_a', 'Correct answer: A. Maintaining up-to-date knowledge and skills', 'intermediate'),
    ('e03b946f-6b19-59ef-9c36-6f1198a4c8ab', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'The EMT-Basic''s role in quality improvement includes all EXCEPT:', 'Documentation', 'Run reviews and audits', 'Performing surgical procedures', 'Gathering feedback from patients', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. Performing surgical procedures', 'intermediate'),
    ('2d1f17d2-430b-52fd-bfab-f65d4c053ff3', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'Which method is commonly used to access the EMS system''', 'Social media', '9-1-1', 'Mail', 'Fax', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. 9-1-1', 'intermediate'),
    ('ace4b4b2-dbaa-5423-996f-eb21737d8eee', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'The health care system components that EMT-Basics interact with include all EXCEPT:', 'Emergency departments', 'Trauma centers', 'Insurance companies', 'Burn centers', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. Insurance companies', 'intermediate'),
    ('d98cfa9d-b2b4-54f5-93fa-76b1ade44966', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'Which is NOT a role or responsibility of the EMT-Basic''', 'Patient assessment', 'Patient care based on assessment findings', 'Prescribing medications', 'Record keeping and data collection', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. Prescribing medications', 'intermediate'),
    ('ed51e735-65d9-5a38-8bc8-fcb32a69ae12', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'The EMT-Basic should maintain current knowledge of:', 'Only local issues', 'Only national issues', 'Local, state, and national issues affecting EMS', 'Only state issues', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. Local, state, and national issues affecting EMS', 'intermediate'),
    ('86beec43-c061-5eb4-8807-dddc906ae340', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'Which public safety workers may EMT-Basics liaise with''', 'Local law enforcement only', 'State law enforcement only', 'Federal law enforcement only', 'Local, state, and federal law enforcement', 'option_d', 'Correct answer: D. Local, state, and federal law enforcement', 'intermediate'),
    ('c2932daa-b80a-5d63-90e8-4a09a621e553', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'The purpose of patient advocacy is to:', 'Make all medical decisions for the patient', 'Treat the patient as a whole, not just the condition', 'Transport the patient against their will', 'Bill the patient for services', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Treat the patient as a whole, not just the condition', 'intermediate'),
    ('9207e480-447a-5b85-b944-02ab9e1d727d', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'What is the recommended response when caring for a patient''', 'Put your safety first, then crew, then patient', 'Put patient needs first without endangering self', 'Always wait for law enforcement before treating', 'Transport only to the closest hospital', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Put patient needs first without endangering self', 'intermediate'),
    ('cf13722d-5990-5cfa-acaf-5142c8f9eb08', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'Which is an example of on-line medical direction''', 'Standing orders', 'Protocols', 'Radio communication with a physician', 'Written guidelines', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. Radio communication with a physician', 'intermediate'),
    ('b1028e77-660b-5266-bdf5-63b4ac494c16', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'The EMT-Basic should maintain current knowledge of:', 'Only local issues', 'Only national issues', 'Local, state, and national issues affecting EMS', 'Only state issues', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. Local, state, and national issues affecting EMS', 'intermediate'),
    ('f93f5dbe-b89d-5459-92fd-8c995c496e11', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-1: Introduction to Emergency Medical Care', 'The relationship between EMT-Basic and hospital personnel is:', 'EMT-Basics work independently from hospital staff', 'EMT-Basics are subordinate to hospital personnel', 'EMT-Basics work side by side with other health care professionals', 'EMT-Basics direct hospital care', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. EMT-Basics work side by side with other health care professionals', 'intermediate'),
    ('6093f7a6-9715-5a7a-b1d4-c025b9f1a225', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'Which of the following is a stage in the dying process according to the curriculum''', 'Happiness', 'Denial', 'Acceptance', 'Both B and C', 'option_d', 'Correct answer: D. Both B and C', 'intermediate'),
    ('cdf5e2df-6ee6-5b87-bf3a-3c00d8da542b', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'In the denial stage of dying, the patient typically:', 'Accepts death calmly', 'Creates a buffer between the shock of dying and dealing with the illness', 'Expresses anger at everyone', 'Retreats into their own world', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Creates a buffer between the shock of dying and dealing with the illness', 'intermediate'),
    ('e5388ac3-9266-5b35-a823-439471d63935', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'During the anger stage of dying, the EMT-Basic should:', 'Argue with the patient', 'Become defensive', 'Be tolerant and not take anger personally', 'Leave the patient alone', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. Be tolerant and not take anger personally', 'intermediate'),
    ('8de36c0e-6ca1-5192-9de4-1aa875dbe1a8', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'Which is an appropriate approach when dealing with a dying patient''', 'False reassurance', 'Use a gentle tone of voice', 'Avoid all physical contact', 'Speak loudly to get their attention', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Use a gentle tone of voice', 'intermediate'),
    ('8f50d59a-5432-54db-ae0c-ceadafdb2584', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'Critical Incident Stress Debriefing (CISD) should be held:', 'Within 24 to 72 hours of a major incident', 'Immediately after the incident', 'One week after the incident', 'Only if requested by the EMT', 'option_a', 'Correct answer: A. Within 24 to 72 hours of a major incident', 'intermediate'),
    ('6bfe16bb-001c-556d-990b-a5bed41953b6', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'Which of the following is a sign of critical incident stress''', 'Increased appetite', 'Irritability to co-workers, family, and friends', 'Improved concentration', 'Decreased anxiety', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Irritability to co-workers, family, and friends', 'intermediate'),
    ('f2999eee-f1e8-520f-9e0d-90f2a333dee7', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'The purpose of Critical Incident Stress Debriefing is to:', 'Assign blame for the incident', 'Accelerate the normal recovery process after experiencing a critical incident', 'Provide legal testimony about the incident', 'Evaluate job performance', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Accelerate the normal recovery process after experiencing a critical incident', 'intermediate'),
    ('97743cd8-3e54-573b-a7db-34673b04ea02', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'Which of the following is a recommended method for managing stress''', 'Increase caffeine intake', 'Reduce sugar, caffeine, and alcohol intake', 'Increase fatty foods', 'Decrease carbohydrates', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Reduce sugar, caffeine, and alcohol intake', 'intermediate'),
    ('ad2be39e-365a-5981-bad6-d1d75b1b3493', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'Body Substance Isolation (BSI) is important for:', 'Protecting the patient''s dignity', 'Protecting the EMT-Basic and patient from infectious diseases', 'Keeping the ambulance clean', 'Reducing patient anxiety', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Protecting the EMT-Basic and patient from infectious diseases', 'intermediate'),
    ('fa9151fc-d378-5e80-b03e-dd565c3ed293', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'Which personal protective equipment is needed for large splash situations such as field delivery''', 'Gloves only', 'Gowns', 'Eye protection only', 'Mask only', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Gowns', 'intermediate'),
    ('d7972903-1c54-5ebc-9afa-8d1958d40650', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'HEPA respirators are needed when:', 'The patient is suspected of having a heart attack', 'The patient is suspected of having tuberculosis', 'The patient is bleeding', 'The patient is in cardiac arrest', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. The patient is suspected of having tuberculosis', 'intermediate'),
    ('64103b34-cff7-5f6b-a3d5-d1af18f2af72', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'When should gloves be changed''', 'Every hour', 'Between contact with different patients', 'At the end of the shift', 'Only when visibly soiled', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Between contact with different patients', 'intermediate'),
    ('9e112725-244f-5301-9cfc-d0b6976b3aa5', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'Which statement about eye protection is correct''', 'Goggles are always required', 'Removable side shields can be applied to prescription eyeglasses', 'Eye protection is optional', 'Sunglasses are sufficient', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Removable side shields can be applied to prescription eyeglasses', 'intermediate'),
    ('33179ac0-f4d8-5a87-a864-1354efcf4219', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'For hazardous materials incidents, EMT-Basics should:', 'Immediately enter the scene to rescue patients', 'Provide care only after the scene is safe and patient contamination is limited', 'Use only gloves for protection', 'Not wait for Haz-Mat teams', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Provide care only after the scene is safe and patient contamination is limited', 'intermediate'),
    ('78b926d8-e82d-5c3f-9da4-843e334bf4a8', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'At a crime scene, the EMT-Basic should:', 'Move everything to access the patient', 'Not disturb the scene unless required for medical care', 'Direct law enforcement personnel', 'Touch weapons to make them safe', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Not disturb the scene unless required for medical care', 'intermediate'),
    ('974aa9aa-69f3-5f58-a372-a9b5cb1cb23e', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'Which is a recommended immunization for EMT-Basics''', 'Hepatitis A vaccine', 'Hepatitis B vaccine', 'Rabies vaccine', 'Yellow fever vaccine', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Hepatitis B vaccine', 'intermediate'),
    ('5ccedbb1-cbe9-5978-8ca9-73bed3f9977c', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'When dealing with a family member who has just lost a loved one, the EMT-Basic should:', 'Offer false reassurance', 'Listen empathetically', 'Avoid all communication', 'Tell them to leave the scene', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Listen empathetically', 'intermediate'),
    ('3d1a2c38-d1ef-5b31-b785-51c69a883cc5', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'Which situation is most likely to produce a stress response in an EMT-Basic''', 'Routine transport', 'Mass casualty situations', 'Documenting a call', 'Restocking the ambulance', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Mass casualty situations', 'intermediate'),
    ('a63f3cfc-ab28-5285-97e3-80ae784a005d', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'What is the benefit of exercise in stress management''', 'It increases stress levels', 'It helps reduce stress', 'It has no effect on stress', 'It only benefits physical health, not mental health', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. It helps reduce stress', 'intermediate'),
    ('4ad200a3-437b-53fe-a62f-9ea01fb14582', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-2: Well-Being of the EMT-Basic', 'When approaching a potentially violent scene, the EMT-Basic should:', 'Enter immediately to assist the patient', 'Wait for law enforcement before providing patient care', 'Bring only essential equipment', 'Approach with sirens on', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Wait for law enforcement before providing patient care', 'intermediate'),
    ('e220ec54-db5a-51f9-8956-f8cdb0094b0e', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'The scope of practice for an EMT-Basic is defined by:', 'The National Registry', 'State legislation', 'The hospital where they work', 'The EMT-Basic themselves', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. State legislation', 'intermediate'),
    ('8884d974-2e5e-5b13-acd3-fe502f64d892', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'Which of the following is an ethical responsibility of the EMT-Basic''', 'Making the physical/emotional needs of the patient a priority', 'Performing procedures beyond their training', 'Avoiding continuing education', 'Charging patients extra for services', 'option_a', 'Correct answer: A. Making the physical/emotional needs of the patient a priority', 'intermediate'),
    ('6f094e7b-29c0-5de5-8574-189bf5a294cf', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'Expressed consent requires that the patient:', 'Be unconscious', 'Be of legal age and able to make a rational decision', 'Have a family member present', 'Be transported to a hospital', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Be of legal age and able to make a rational decision', 'intermediate'),
    ('bd882ed1-2882-5486-a1ba-144298fb5bc6', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'Implied consent is based on the assumption that:', 'The patient is conscious', 'The unconscious patient would consent to life-saving interventions', 'The family always agrees to treatment', 'The patient''s insurance covers all procedures', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. The unconscious patient would consent to life-saving interventions', 'intermediate'),
    ('5012438b-a9f8-5306-a4bc-ba857f172d37', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'For a minor child requiring emergency care, consent should be obtained from:', 'The child', 'The parent or legal guardian', 'The school nurse', 'The police', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. The parent or legal guardian', 'intermediate'),
    ('9e3a0ff4-a864-50ef-8f30-3705cc80eb0c', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'What is the EMT-Basic''s legal obligation regarding a patient''s refusal of transport''', 'Transport the patient against their will', 'Force treatment on the patient', 'Inform the patient of risks and consequences, document, and have patient sign refusal form', 'Leave immediately without explanation', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. Inform the patient of risks and consequences, document, and have patient sign refusal form', 'intermediate'),
    ('004b1cd1-c5ac-5753-ae5a-9c2437c02b9c', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'Abandonment occurs when:', 'A patient is left at the hospital', 'Care is terminated without assuring continuation of care at the same or higher level', 'An ambulance leaves the scene', 'A patient refuses care', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Care is terminated without assuring continuation of care at the same or higher level', 'intermediate'),
    ('9c0b91e8-acc6-59eb-abc4-1eb529115bba', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'Which component is NOT required to prove negligence''', 'Duty to act', 'Breach of the duty', 'Patient''s consent', 'Injury/damages were caused by the EMT-Basic''s actions', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. Patient''s consent', 'intermediate'),
    ('e6659a8f-5032-57a5-b165-8429db055ee0', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'A Do Not Resuscitate (DNR) order:', 'Means no care should be provided at all', 'Allows the patient to refuse resuscitative efforts', 'Is always valid in the field', 'Can be verbal only', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Allows the patient to refuse resuscitative efforts', 'intermediate'),
    ('d451db96-b827-512f-8272-49ab217131fa', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'When in doubt about a DNR order, the EMT-Basic should:', 'Not resuscitate', 'Begin resuscitation efforts', 'Wait for family to decide', 'Call the medical examiner', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Begin resuscitation efforts', 'intermediate'),
    ('029ff8a3-3344-5f40-b737-9cf57cd07478', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'Patient confidentiality requires that:', 'All patient information can be shared with anyone', 'Patient history and assessment findings are kept confidential', 'Only the patient''s name is confidential', 'Information can be released without consent', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Patient history and assessment findings are kept confidential', 'intermediate'),
    ('9a4a2a21-34fc-569e-9989-5a816a83cef9', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'Which situation allows release of confidential patient information without written consent''', 'The patient''s employer requests it', 'The patient''s neighbor asks about the call', 'Other health care providers need information to continue care', 'The media requests information', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. Other health care providers need information to continue care', 'intermediate'),
    ('0b6848a7-7a42-5e5a-9fb7-00ab380ac9b4', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'What is the EMT-Basic''s responsibility regarding organ donors''', 'Identify the patient as a potential donor and provide care to maintain viable organs', 'Harvest organs in the field', 'Transport organs instead of the patient', 'Disregard donor status during emergencies', 'option_a', 'Correct answer: A. Identify the patient as a potential donor and provide care to maintain viable organs', 'intermediate'),
    ('76d395aa-6001-5dcf-95e3-1e78063e679f', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'At a crime scene, the EMT-Basic should prioritize:', 'Evidence preservation over patient care', 'Emergency care of the patient', 'Photography of the scene', 'Interviewing witnesses', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Emergency care of the patient', 'intermediate'),
    ('254f4b29-3bd1-56a1-9c6e-ca45c71362c7', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'Which situation requires mandatory reporting to law enforcement''', 'Any medical emergency', 'Suspected child abuse', 'Heart attack', 'Stroke', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Suspected child abuse', 'intermediate'),
    ('594dde7c-f91e-5127-85f9-f35f6cc07d81', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'Assault and battery in EMS refers to:', 'Performing emergency care correctly', 'Unlawfully touching a patient without consent', 'Transporting a patient to the hospital', 'Taking vital signs', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Unlawfully touching a patient without consent', 'intermediate'),
    ('8d5f9d85-a806-5329-a8c6-e01838453c37', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'The EMT-Basic has a duty to act when:', 'Always, regardless of circumstances', 'A contractual or legal obligation exists', 'Off duty and observing an accident', 'Never, unless paid', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. A contractual or legal obligation exists', 'intermediate'),
    ('c74f6f27-5d33-5811-bf0d-f3f92ba455f1', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'A patient who withdraws from treatment after initially consenting:', 'Must continue treatment', 'Can withdraw at any time if mentally competent', 'Must wait for the EMT to finish', 'Needs police permission', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Can withdraw at any time if mentally competent', 'intermediate'),
    ('819a0ff7-34fa-5ed4-8778-7602fe71a114', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'Before leaving a patient who refuses transport, the EMT-Basic should:', 'Leave immediately', 'Try again to persuade the patient, ensure rational decision, and document', 'Force the patient to go', 'Call the police to arrest the patient', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Try again to persuade the patient, ensure rational decision, and document', 'intermediate'),
    ('0a3ac6c9-250a-575d-9373-b040a2de2ed7', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-3: Medical/Legal and Ethical Issues', 'The legal term for deviation from accepted standard of care resulting in further injury is:', 'Abandonment', 'Battery', 'Negligence', 'Assault', 'option_c', 'Correct answer: C. Negligence', 'intermediate'),
    ('9b2c45c8-888b-5651-abae-61802d9c9e1b', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-4: The Human Body', 'The term "medial" means:', 'Away from the midline', 'Toward the midline', 'Toward the front', 'Toward the back', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Toward the midline', 'intermediate'),
    ('9d1416a0-bd88-5096-9ce8-c327eac5a5ac', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-4: The Human Body', 'The term "lateral" means:', 'Toward the midline', 'Away from the midline', 'Toward the head', 'Toward the feet', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Away from the midline', 'intermediate'),
    ('5b8abaf3-888e-5d2d-8a9e-9ea60ce19669', 'PREPARATORY', 'Lesson 1-4: The Human Body', '"Proximal" means:', 'Farther from the trunk', 'Closer to the trunk', 'Toward the feet', 'Toward the front', 'option_b', 'Correct answer: B. Closer to the trunk', 'intermediate'),
